{It is usually not recommended to use any form of Blackwood when you have a suit with two quick 
losers, but SOUTH knows NORTH would not preempt with a 10-high \H suit.

NORTH's reply to RKCB is 5\H, showing two Key Cards. 
SOUTH knows they are the \HA \HK 
so she can count thirteen tricks.

She bids a confident 7NT (and hopes NORTH didn't open 3\H with a 6-card suit.}

